So, if you have a CZ52, it's a strong well made pistol and should be fine, but if you have a Tokarev, Broomhandle, or other antique, you should probably skip the military stuff. Shoot often, but shoot safe. I can't do pictures.

title: For Sale:  The "Nearly Perfect" Rifle Battery ~                                    Collectors Set of Four Winchester Model 70 Supergrades
postcontent:
This rifle set was only made available to members of the Midway USA Scholastic Shooting Trust for fundraising.  Only 100 sets were produced.  Proceeds from this sale will go directly to the Bishop Dwenger Rifle Team, a new team with aspirations of building an indoor shooting sports facility capable of hosting international level events.  Midway will match the proceeds of the sale three fold to the rifle team.  

No other rifle holds the power and the mystique of the legendary Winchester Model 70 Super Grade – the ultimate expression of the Rifleman’s Rifle.  For the first time ever, The Midway Foundation is proud to offer a matching set of four truly unique limited production Winchester Model 70 Super Grade rifles, each of which is chambered in a cartridge that’s ideal for the game animals they commemorate, and is so marked on the magazine floorplate.  The Varmint rifle is chambered in the blistering 22-250 Remington, the Deer/Antelope in the flat shooting 270 Winchester, the Elk/Moose in the potent 300 Winchester Magnum and the Dangerous Game rifle in the bore crushing 375 H&H Magnum.  All of the classic Model 70 Super Grade features are present – the fancy grade checkered walnut stock with shadowline cheeckpiece and ebony fore-end tip, the engraved crossbolt head and the traditional Super Grade pistol grip cap.  Each of these beautiful rifles is built with the Pre-’64 style action that offers a forged steel receiver, massive external claw extractor, controlled round feeding and reliable blade ejection.

title: For Sale:  AK47 Mak-90 Poly Tech Norinco Milled 386
postcontent:
Here is a safe queen Milled AK 47 manufactured in the Poly Tech plant 386. Please understand; this is not your average AK 47. The receiver on this is machined from a solid block of steel instead of sheetmetal stamped and riveted together like most. I bought three of these still in plastic and smothered in cosmoline. I removed the deteriorated plastic wrapping, wiped down the outside, attached the slings, and stored them away. There is still cosmoline on the interior parts and the wood is very nice with minimal markings. This numbers matching rifle was imported by IDE in Michigan and I believe it to be unfired. The authentic boxes are gone but the original 10 round mag is included and 30 round magazines are still easily available. The milled versions are the most accurate and strong enough to handle modifications for SHTF scenarios. The one piece Monte Carlo stocks are much more durable than pistol grips. The more modern AR15s are nice to have but the AKs are a larger caliber and will operate much better in a more severe environment, sand, mud, cold, and wet. And they gain in value similar to other precious metals.
 I decided to let go of one before the election while it is still legal to sell, who knows what the future will bring? November 6th is right around the corner.  Along with the potential for economic meltdown there are numerous threats of riots and unrest by people who may not get their way, so don't wait until it is too late. title: For Sale:  AK47 Mak-90 Milled Receiver Poly Tech Norinco 386
location: Iowa Quad Cities, Quad Cities, Illinois
postcontent:
Here is a safe queen Milled AK 47 manufactured in the Poly Tech plant 386. Please understand; this is not your average AK 47. The receiver on this is machined from a solid block of steel instead of sheetmetal stamped and riveted together like most. I bought three of these still in plastic and smothered in cosmoline. I removed the deteriorated plastic wrapping, wiped down the outside, attached the slings, and stored them away. There is still cosmoline on the interior parts and the wood is very nice with minimal markings. This numbers matching rifle was imported by IDE in Michigan and I believe it to be unfired. The authentic boxes are gone but the original 10 round mag is included and 30 round magazines are still easily available. The milled versions are the most accurate and strong enough to handle modifications for SHTF scenarios. The one piece Monte Carlo stocks are much more durable than pistol grips. The more modern AR15s are nice to have but the AKs are a larger caliber and will operate much better in a more severe environment, sand, mud, cold, and wet. And they gain in value similar to other precious metals.
 I decided to let go of one before the election while it is still legal to sell, who knows what the future will bring? November 6th is right around the corner as is the potential for economic meltdown so don't wait until it is too late.

Shipping outside of Iowa to your FFL will be actual cost, or I may be able to take to an Illinois QC FFL dealer to transfer. I will be happy to do a Face-to-Face with Iowa ID. Any questions ? REDACTED Warren
